title: Grateful Dead Live at Sam Boyd Silver Bowl on 1992-05-31
lineage: Sony TC-WE635 (Dolby C decoded) > Tascam DR-680 > SDHC card > PC > WaveLab 5 > CD Wave Editor 1.95.1 > Flac Frontend 1.7.1 > Flac; Taped and Transferred by Chuck Miller
description:
Set 1

Help On The Way > Slipknot! > Franklin's Tower, Minglewood Blues, It Must Have Been The Roses, Queen Jane Approximately, Bird Song, Picasso Moon

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias > Fire On The Mountain, Women Are Smarter > So Many Roads, Saint Of Circumstance > He's Gone > Drums > Space > Attics Of My Life, Spoonful* > The Other One* > Morning Dew*

E: Baba O'Riley* > Tomorrow Never Knows*

University Of Nevada At Las Vegas

* - w/ Steve Miller

reviews.review_text: Slow Loping Slipknot Thanx Chuck.  I really like this show.  A very nice recording to boot.  My cassette had the Dew cutting close to the peak of the last jam (even had to write a caution on the tape cover to avoid cardiac arrest, no Dew should cut at the end).  Happily this one is complete.  A very thick Dew, with some great work by Steve.  Check out the Spooonful/Other One segue.  Before the pschedelic jams begin, the blues jam keeps pulling them back.  TNK has great sounds and love the effects on drums.  I played Space thru morning Dew on my radio show (KHSU) tonight.  Not sure if this one merits 5 stars but I damn sure can't give it 4.  Peace

- Not the worst dead show I ever saw, but maybe the most unfocused. Morning dew rips, and the baba tomorrow is fun. Garcia was having guitar problems...actually I think the whole sound system was squirrels that day. Was up close right in front of Garcia. At one point in Picasso he was just standing there looking silly because he couldn't get a sound outta his axe.
